      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">column</rs> capital</rs>, with the <rs type="decoration">bust</rs> of a man protruding from it (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.25</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.62</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.705</measure>). The head, which has been broken, interrupted the upper rim of the moulding.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p>The inscription runs in one line on the upper rim, which is broken at the right.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p><measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.045</measure>; tall and thin.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0301" notAfter="0500">Fourth/fifth century</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="la" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
        <ab><lb n="1"/><g type="cross"/> <rs key="acclamations" type="subject"><w lemma="felix">Felix</w> <w lemma="semper">semper </w></rs><g type="head"/> <persName key="Scholasticius" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Scholasticius">Scholast<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">icius</supplied></name></persName></ab>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>May Scholastikios always be fortunate!</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="V.60">V.60</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p><rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">City, Village</rs>: re-used in a house near the Theatre.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Unknown.</rs>. <rs type="lastLocation">Museum.</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
        <head>History of Recording</head>
        <p>Found by the NYU expedition in 1969 during destruction of village houses (<rs type="invNo">69.308</rs>).</p>
      </div>

